profile_positions.description:
Mr. Tyler has brought extensive professional experience and holistic leadership to GSI; with an expansive career spanning Aerospace/ Defense, Banking, Energy, Finance, HealthCare, Legal, Manufacturing, Non-Profit, Petra-Chemical, Government, Trade, Transportation/Shipping and Technology.  Jesse’s skill set is multi-layered; with emphasis in economic development, finance, marketing, operations and program management.  

As an independent consultant, Mr. Tyler transferred the aforementioned skills to the Los Angeles Urban League; wherein he provided vital management and technical assistance to over 90 SME firms every year across a myriad of industry sectors as Managing Consultant at their Business Center.

At GSI, Mr. Tyler provided strategic leadership, implementation of our intelligent systems and life-cycle management of the firm’s projects - as GSI works to enjoy continual growth now and into the foreseeable future.

 Mr. Tyler holds dual degrees in Finance and Economics from the Myhalio School at CSU Fullerton and has done extensive graduate work in Finance at USC Marshall.
